	<h1>
		Key Risks</h1>
	<p>
		&bull;Investment is in a private limited company (a &ldquo;Company&rdquo;) which has no secondary market. Value is realised by the sale of the underlying trading activities. Under certain market conditions, shareholders seeking to redeem their holdings may experience significant delays;</p>
	<p>
		&bull;The value of an investment and any income from them may fall as well as rise and is not guaranteed; &bull;The past performance of any Company or underlying trading activity is not a reliable indicator of future results &bull;The value of the real assets employed by a trading activity will generally be a matter of valuer&#39;s opinion, rather than fact, and may fall as well as rise;</p>
	<p>
		&bull;All information is based upon current taxation and other legislation including the current rate of Business Property Relief (100%): any changes in the legislation may affect the value of an investment and the availability of Business Property Relief. The tax treatment depends on the individual circumstances of each shareholder and may be subject to change in the future;</p>
	<p>
		&bull;The success the underlying trading activities in which a Company participates is dependent in part on the continued performance of the appointed third party advisers. &nbsp; The insolvency or other financial difficulties of any such party will have an adverse effect on the success of the relevant activity;</p>
	<p>
		&bull;A shareholder may get back less than the original amount invested. In certain circumstances, shareholders may not receive back any monies invested in some trading activities;</p>
	<p>
		&bull;An investment are not covered by the Financial Services Compensation Scheme established by the Financial Services Authority or by any other compensation scheme;</p>
	<p>
		&bull;Investment is only possible via the Information Memorandum.</p>
	<p>
		The foregoing list of risk factors is not comprehensive and the attention of prospective shareholders is drawn both to the specific risk factors set out for each CTC Project as well as to the more general risk factors of CTC, all of which are contained within the Information Memorandum.</p>
